**Every day, people create amazing solutions at EPAM. Imagine, what you could do!**

Our customer is the second-largest British bank, one of the largest commercial
banks in Scotland that provides banking facilities throughout the UK and
Ireland.

We are looking for our team: **Senior QA ****Engineer**

Required skills and experience:

  * At least 3 years of **software test automation experience** using an industry standard test automation tool;
  * Good understanding of test automation approach;
  * Perform test automation tasks, solve test automation issues by standard capabilities of test automation tools;
  * Experienced with **real time business critical systems**;
  * Experience with **Linux****  
**
  * Experience in **DB testing, **preferrably **SQL**
  * Fluency in English and good English writing skills to liaise with other teams, support staff, end users, and business management people;
  * Candidate should be a team player, self-motivated, well-organized, strong communicator, driven and committed;
  * Must be able to work in a fast paced environment, with strict timescales;
  * Open for traveling.

Advantages will be experience with:

  * **Agile Development Experience;**
  * Experience with the FIX protocol;
  * Testing experience (TDD/ATDD);
  * Experience with electronic trading platforms within financial institutions;
  * OO development experience with Java server-side development;
  * Continuous Integration (Jenkins, Bamboo);
  * Rule engine knowledge (e.g. Drools);
  * NoSQL, cloud development experience.

EPAM offers:

  * Attractive salary, additional **health and dental insurance** as long as other **social benefits;**
  * **Personal development** program that will allow people to be valued for their**strengths;**
  * Wide range of **professional trainings** and workshops;
  * **Broad projects** variety and** possible mobility** between projects over the time;
  * **Experience exchange** with colleagues around the world;
  * **Work-life balance** and flexible schedule, team buildings and sport opportunities;
  * Modern office in the **Infinity Tower** business center. 

About us

EPAM Systems is an **US based** software services and solutions provider
ranked **#1 in Central and Eastern Europe** with over 15 000 employees. From
software products to core business applications, EPAM has provided expert
consulting, development, testing, support and infrastructure services to many
of the world’s leading organizations. As the world of technology has evolved,
so has our distributed delivery model, which now includes advanced
capabilities in running **Agile and Lean engagements. **Recognized as a Leader
in Product Development in CEE - we have just opened our **office in Sofia**
and you have a unique chance to be a member of our Bulgarian team from the
very beginning. Join us now!

_ _

_If you are interested in this role please send your CV in English.  
All applications will be treated as strictly confidential._

_Only short-listed applicants will be contacted._

|  KPMG IT Service is a joint company of KPMG Germany and KPMG Bulgaria. The
company employs top IT talent for its operations in Sofia in the fields of
Software Engineering, Cloud Computing, Collaboration, Applications Operations
and IT Operations.  
We are now looking for SAP UI5 / SAP ABAP Developer.  

Main responsibilities include:  

• Documentation of comprehensive SAP based applications (FI/CO, HR);  
• Development within innovation projects (new UIs based on Fiori/SAPUI5);  
• Solution maintenance and troubleshooting;  

Required skills and experience:  

• Bachelor's degree in Computer Science or similar university degree;  
• Advanced knowledge of ABAP / ABAP OO is mandatory;  
• Knowledge in at least one of the modules is required: FI/CO, HR;  
• Advanced knowledge of JavaScript, JQuery or HTML5 is mandatory;  
• Very good knowledge of English (written and verbal);  
• Ability to travel to Germany on business trips;  

The skills below are not mandatory but will be considered an advantage:  

• Experience in developing SAP Fiori/UI5 applications, which goes beyond the
pure customization;  
• Knowledge in SAP Gateway and oData modelling;  
• Knowledge in PI/PO process integration;  
• Knowledge in SAP HANA;  
• Experience in SAP Archiving  

What we offer:  

• The chance to work in a top talent team  
• Attractive remuneration  
• Opportunity to work with cutting-edge technologies  
• Gain experience in an international and multicultural organization  
• Opportunity for business travel  
• Work on challenging projects  
• Modern office environment  
• Additional health insurance  
• Life insurance  
• Free transportation card  
• Free sports facility card  
• Option to work from home  

We invite you to take up this challenge! If interested send me your CV.  

