• Experience in customer handling will be an advantage;  

So join our team of upbeat professionals and support some of the most
successful organizations on the planet! It is people just like YOU that make
TeleTech a great place to work at.

|  СИЕНСИС АД е в ТОП 3 на системни интегратори на българския ИТ пазар,
предлагащ цялостни инфраструктурни решения като база за изграждане на
софтуерни системи и управленски приложения с продукти и технологии на Hewlett-
Packard , Cisco Systems, EMC, Hewlett-Packard Software, Microsoft, Oracle и
VMware.  
Екипът на компанията предлага модерни компютърни решения и комплексни ИТ
инфраструктурни системи за нуждите на малък и среден бизнес, корпоративни
клиенти и големи организации в България.  

Във връзка с разрастване на нашия екип търсим да назначим:  

СПЕЦИАЛИСТ ПОДДРЪЖКА НА ИТ ИНФРАСТРУКТУРА  

ИЗИСКВАНИЯ:  
\- Опит в следните системни технологии : Windows/Linux сървърни OS;  
\- Опит във виртуализационни технологии : Vmware, Microsoft;  
\- Опит в следните мрежови технологии : LAN, WAN, Security, SAN;  
\- Оознания в областта на проектиране, изграждане и обслужване на
изчислителните центрове (Data Center);  
\- Задълбочени познания в някоя от продуктовите гами на HPE, DELL/EMC, Cisco
Systems, IBM, LENOVO, Checkpoint, Juniper, Fortinet, F5;  
\- Аналитично мислене и способност за решаване на проблеми;  
\- Умение за работа в екип и с външни за организацията клиенти;  

ЗАДЪЛЖЕНИЯ:  
\- Извършва инсталации, конфигурации и тестове на IT оборудване в изчислителни
центрове (Data Center);  
\- Участва в поддръжката на системите в изчислителни центрове (Data Center)  
\- Извършва инженерни консултации;  
\- Участва в екипи по изготвяне на предложения за дизайн, инсталация и
поддръжка на системи в изчислителни центрове (Data Center);  
\- Изготвя проектна документация;  

ПРЕДИМСТВО:  
\- Сертификат или преминати обучения: HP ASE, HP MASE, CCIP, CCDP, CCNP
Security, CCIE, Checkpoint CCSA/CCSE, Juniper JNCIA/JNCIE, Fortinet/Fortigate
certification, EMC Technology Architect, Oracle Exadata, DELL Enterprise, IBM
PowerX, IBM Storages или техни еквиваленти;  

НИЕ ПРЕДЛАГАМЕ:  
\- Възможност за работа с най-новите технологии и продукти на световните
лидери в областта на изграждане и обслужване на изчислителните центрове (Data
Center);  
\- Отлични условия на труд;  
\- Работа в сплотен екип от доказани специалисти;  
\- Възможност за професионално развитие и обучения в центровете на световните
ИТ технологични лидери;  
\- Конкурентно възнаграждение;  

Ако нашето предложение за работа представлява интерес за Вас и желаете да се
присъедините към нашия екип от професионалисти, можете да кандидатствате като
изпратите актуална автобиография със снимка.  

Моля, посочвайте Ref.N на позицията, за която кандидатствате.  

Контакт ще бъде установен само с одобрените по документи кандидати.  

Всяка получена информация ще се третира съгласно ЗЗЛД.

|

**STUDIO PROFILE**

Established in 2006, Ubisoft Sofia has quickly become one of the group’s most
versatile studios. In its first 6 years, the studio has already developed a
rich portfolio, ranging from casual games to flight simulations, and covering
a wide range of platforms and technologies:_Tom Clancy’s Ghost Recon® Shadow
Wars 3DS, Prince of Persia® Trilogy HD PS3, Imagine® Fashion Designer 3DS,
Prince of Persia® Classics PSN, Chessmaster® The Art of Learning DS &amp; PSP_
and many more. The studio’s latest achievements include the successful
development of _Assassin’s Creed III Liberation for PS VITA, Assassin’s Creed
4: Black Flag_ (alongside Ubisoft Montreal and 5 other studios), _Assassin’s
Creed Liberation HD_ and most recently_Assassin’s Creed Rogue_.

**  

ROLE**  
The Gameplay Programmer develops gameplay elements which facilitate the
playability of the game (the link between the player's actions, character's
behavior, and the consequences on the evolution of the game) and complex
gameplay mechanisms.

**JOB RESPONSIBILITIES**

  * Uses his/her technical knowledge to simulate believable behaviors;
  * May be required to simulate a complex AI by using simple algorithms;
  * Identifies missing details in feature requests and can break down the tasks into parts that can be implemented and tested;
  * Analyzes the game and level design in order to give feedback on their feasibility;
  * Works closely with team members of own or other job families for the optimal development of assigned features, during all stages of the development process;
  * Participates in prototyping of features and is able to define their own objectives;
  * Carries out RIP (Rapid Iterative Playtests) on their prototypes;
  * Analyzes unfamiliar code of moderate complexity to understand the functionality of an existing module;
  * Re-uses existing code effectively;
  * Debugs defects of moderate complexity and ensures that problem has been fully solved;
  * Identifies and corrects other bugs discovered along the way, even if outside his/her scope of work;
  * Creates latency-free, reactive interactions;
  * Uses metrics to detect regressions in the general gameplay that harm the game feel;
  * Produces efficient software design and participates in software design reviews;
  * Writes Portable Code (writes project specific code where appropriate);
  * Writes code that is modular and self-contained.

**  
QUALIFICATIONS**

  * Enthusiasm and desire to work in the game development industry;
  * Ability and desire to work in creative and collaborative teams;
  * Good knowledge of C++ and object-oriented development;
  * Some understanding of meta programming techniques;
  * Basic knowledge of templates and design patterns and anti-patterns;
  * Strong knowledge of the software development environment and associated tools (i.e. Visual Studio, Perforce, etc.);
  * Knowledge of at least one scripting language;
  * Ability to write clear, concise code &amp; documentation;
  * Ability to judge and communicate on the potential impact of his changes;
  * Ability to understand and apply the rational design methods;
  * Some knowledge of planning and monitoring tools (Jira, Excel);
  * Good MS Office skills (Word, Outlook, PowerPoint);
  * Good communication skills;
  * Interest in computer and video games;
  * Ability to manage their own time and work within deadlines;
  * Good English skills;
  * Minimum 2 (two) years of experience; experience in games development will be a plus.

**  
WE OFFER**

  * Professional working environment and access to new technologies;
  * Career opportunities, including the possibility of professional exchanges with other Ubisoft studios around the world;
  * Incentive programs meant to ensure our new employees an easy integration in the teams;
  * Motivating salary and bonuses;
  * Comprehensive benefits package, incl. meal tickets, transport titles, private medical insurance, etc.;
  * International work culture;
  * Excellent office location._  
_

_  
Location: Sofia, Bulgaria (work on-site)_

|  Software AG Development Center Bulgaria, a subsidiary of Software AG, is
one of the fastest growing software companies in Bulgaria. We have established
a technology development office in the heart of Sofia focused on development
and enhancement of our SOA suite. We are looking for Junior Cloud Service
Operations Engineer to join our team.  

ABOUT THE JOB  

Be an active member of the Sofia Cloud operations hub, develop and maintain
the systems that comprise the backbone of the Cloud Operations tools and
utilities;  
Manage Software AG Cloud environments for stability, security, and
satisfaction for optimal customer experiences to grow Software AG Cloud
business;  
Setup and maintain multiple cloud Dev / QA / Staging / production
environments;  
Work closely with development teams, Global Support Organization and Product
Management;  
Establish and enforce standards and procedures for the installation and
maintenance of systems and data;  
Occasionally participate in weekend support on-call (standby shift);  
Implement and audit security controls, governance processes, and compliance
validation according to security and compliance requirements;  

ABOUT YOU  

2+ years of experience in technology and/or production operations management
and/or information security;  
Willingness to manage cloud production operations (AWS);  
Systems knowledge (Linux);  
Excellent oral and written English communication skills;  

Demonstrate at least 1 skill area of IT disciplines in the context of web
Applications:  
DevOps / Config Engineering (Automation – conceptual level)  
Scripting knowledge (anyone of Python / Bash / Perl)  
Security Processes knowledge (SIEM)  

Skills which are a plus:  
Knowledge of cloud relevant security standards like ISO 27K, SOC (1/2/3), CSA,
etc.;  
Degree in Information Technology, Computer Science, or Business Information
Systems;  
Network admin (VPN, firewalls);  
Database admin (Oracle/MySQL);  
Knowledge of IT management frameworks is a plus (ITIL etc.);  
IT support and customer facing experience.  

WHAT YOU CAN EXPECT  

An opportunity to work on some of the most important and challenging Software
AG products used by large enterprises all over the world;  
Excellent remuneration package with additional social and medical benefits;  
Work-life balance - 25 days of vacation, flexible working hours, home office
policy;  
Well-defined career and personal development opportunities in wide range of
technology areas;  
Regular training and team building events;  
A sustainable job in a global environment;  
Fun and comfortable working atmosphere.  

OUR PROFILE  
Software AG is the global leader in Business Process Excellence. We are
offering software and service solutions for process strategy, design,
integration and control; SOA-based integration and data management; process-
driven SAP implementation; and strategic process consulting and services. Our
